@startuml
title Operate fiscal core — top system lifecycle master

hide footbox
autonumber 10 10
skinparam BoxPadding 12
skinparam SequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam Shadowing false
skinparam ParticipantPadding 18
skinparam ResponseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam DefaultFontName Monospace

actor "Operator /\nBusiness Application" as ACT

box "Open Fiscal Core — System Components" #F3F3F3
  boundary "ESIR" as ESIR <<component>>
  control  "E-SDC" as ESDC <<component>>
end box

box "External Dependencies" #EEF5FF
  control  "V-SDC\n(TaxCore Cloud)" as VSDC <<external>>
  entity   "SE\n(Security Element)" as SE <<external>>
  entity   "PKI Applet /\nClient Certificate" as PKI <<external>>
  control  "TaxCore.API Shared" as TCS <<external>>
  control  "TaxCore Backend\n(E-SDC API)" as TCB <<external>>
  storage  "Removable Media\n(SD Card / USB)" as MEDIA <<external>>
  boundary "Public Verification" as PV <<external>>
end box

note over ACT, PV #FFF8DC
S_SYS_OPERATE_FISCAL_CORE_MASTER
[semantics lifecycle_spine=true]
end note

note over ESIR, TCB
  Top-level lifecycle master.
  Each group below is elaborated by its own system scenario.
  This diagram shows operational scope and sequencing,
  not full protocol detail.
end note

group S1 "Establish bootstrap and configuration"
  ref over ACT, ESIR, ESDC, PKI, TCS, TCB
    S_SYS_BOOTSTRAP_AND_CONFIGURATION
  end ref
end

group S2 "Establish readiness and operator recovery"
  ref over ACT, ESIR, ESDC, SE
    S_SYS_STATUS_AND_OPERATOR_RECOVERY
  end ref
end

group S3 "Fiscalize invoice"
  ref over ACT, ESIR, ESDC, VSDC, SE, TCB
    S_SYS_FISCALIZE_INVOICE
  end ref
end

group S4 "Maintain backend sync and command lifecycle"
  ref over ESDC, TCB
    S_SYS_BACKEND_SYNC_AND_COMMAND_LIFECYCLE
  end ref
end

group S5 "Maintain audit and proof lifecycle"
  ref over ESDC, SE, TCB
    S_SYS_AUDIT_AND_PROOF_LIFECYCLE
  end ref
end

group S6 "Perform local audit export"
  ref over ACT, ESDC, SE, MEDIA
    S_SYS_LOCAL_AUDIT_EXPORT
  end ref
end

group S7 "Expose public verification"
  ref over ACT, ESIR, PV
    S_SYS_PUBLIC_VERIFICATION
  end ref
end

note over ESIR, ESDC
  ESIR owns business-facing orchestration.
  E-SDC owns secure-element interaction,
  backend synchronization, audit transfer,
  proof-of-audit completion,
  and local audit export handling.
end note

note over TCS, TCB
  Shared TaxCore services provide bootstrap data.
  E-SDC backend provides token, commands,
  audit submission, and proof-related backend flows.
end note

@enduml